<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Learning about display property in css</title>
<style>

/* display  : none ->  it will remove the block and also space*/
/* visibility : hidden -> it will temperory remove the block as per visibility and space will never be removed */
/* to do this preview me jake embedded preview enable krna hai and live preview ko off  */
*{
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}
.L{
    border :2px solid yellow;
    display : inline-block;
    margin: 50px;
    padding : 40px;
    display : inline-flex;
    justify-content : space-between;
}

.dabba{
    border: 2px solid red;
    /* display: inline;  this will not give margin from top so we use inline block */

    display: inline-block;
    margin : 59px;
    padding : 40px;
    /* using display:inline we can make a block element behave like an inline element  */
}

</style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="dabba">
        <p>I am a box yooooo!</p>
    </div>
    <div class="L">
        <p>I am another box yooooo!</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
